APCu NEWS

(unreleased)
- Added apc.mmap_shared_file: back the APCu segment with a fixed-path file so
  unrelated processes (CLI and web SAPIs) share one user cache. See
  SHARED_SEGMENT.md.
- Added apcu_rotate_segment() and apcu_segment_refresh() for live segment
  rotation and resizing, with automatic re-attach.
- Added apc.mmap_shared_file_fallback to degrade to a private segment instead
  of aborting startup on an operational shared-segment failure.
- Fixed apc_unpersist_ht() to re-resolve the HashTable destructor locally, so
  entries stored by one binary can be safely read by another (required for
  cross-process sharing; harmless under the previous fork-only model).
